                            <comment id="308608" author="arshad512" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2021 00:19:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andreas, yes. I will take this up. Opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14889&quot; title=&quot;checksum_type support for server&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14889&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14889&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="308599" author="adilger" created="Tue, 27 Jul 2021 23:04:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Arshad, one thing I noticed is that there are &quot;{&lt;tt&gt;osc,mdc}.&amp;#42;.checksum_type&lt;/tt&gt; files on the client, but there are no corresponding &quot;{&lt;tt&gt;mdt,ofd}.&amp;#42;.checksum_type&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; files on the servers that report which checksum types are currently supported.  It isn&apos;t possible to see this just from the client-side &lt;tt&gt;checksum_type&lt;/tt&gt; because those may only list the fastest subset of types reported by the server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would you be interested to implement this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
